_Ménilmuche_ writes on his [blog](http://menilmontant.typepad.fr/) [fr] about
the [evacuation of “La Maison des Étudiants de l’Ouest
Africain”](http://menilmontant.typepad.fr/mon_weblog/2010/10/la-maison-des-
etudiants-de-louest-africain-evacuee.html) [fr]. In 1950 [Colonial period],
French West Africa ([AOF](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_West_Africa))
purchased this building to house the elected West African representatives. The
building became a student dormitory in the 1960's when the countries reached[
independence](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/17/africa-colonialism-
alive-and-well-after-50-years-of-independence/). However Benin, Burkina Faso,
Côte d'Ivoire, Mali, Mauritania, Niger and Senegal have [lost interest in
maintaining the building for years
now](http://www.lefaso.net/spip.php?article33022)[fr].

